JOHANNESBURG - A Gupta-owned company allegedly paid for a luxury Dubai hotel room for Communications Minister, Ayanda Dlodlo.Sahara Computers reportedly paid for Dlodlo's Dubai trip in 2015. Leaked emails show her bills were settled by the controversial businessman, Fana Hlongwane.Cabinet reshuffle: Meet SA's new ministersDlodlo confirmed the trip, saying she maintains a professional relationship with Hlongwane.She says she was en route to Jordan but stopped in Dubai for a meeting. Invoices for the trip include a hired car, accommodation and spa massages.eNCA